    },
    {
      "type": "latex_inline",
      "content": "are the marginal distributions of X and Y obtained through a marginalization process. Note that in the context of time series, both X and Y are continuous variables.\n\nConceptually, MI quantifies the a",
      "start": 14072,
      "end": 15711
    },
    {
      "type": "latex_inline",
      "content": "to approximate the mutual information I(X,Y) between random variables X and Y [52].\n\n<span id=\"page-2-2\"></span>",
      "start": 15732,
      "end": 15849
    },
    {
      "type": "latex_inline",
