      "start": 16411,
      "end": 16439
    },
    {
      "type": "latex_inline",
      "content": "is a critic function aiming to distinguish whether the x and y come from the same joint distribution, and Z(y) is the associated partition function.\n\nIf we use different techniques to deal with the fa",
      "start": 16492,
      "end": 18831
    },
    {
      "type": "latex_inline",
      "content": "is treated as D univariate time series",
      "start": 18870,
      "end": 18914
    },
    {
      "type": "latex_inline",
      "content": ". The univariate time series are each standardized and partitioned into overlapping subsequences by using a sliding window of length B. Then, the resulting sequences of length B, are fed into the mode",
      "start": 18973,
      "end": 20052
    },
    {
      "type": "latex_inline",
      "content": "\\mathbf{H}_{t:t+B} = \\frac{\\mathbf{s}_{t:t+B} - \\mathbb{E}[\\mathbf{s}_{t:t+B}]}{\\sqrt{\\text{Var}[\\mathbf{s}_{t:t+B}] + \\epsilon}} \\cdot \\gamma_1 + \\beta_1",
